To begin with, we define the matrix \emph{A}:

\texttt{~~~A~=~{[}1~1~0~1~0;~2~2~1~3~0;~3~3~1~4~1;~4~4~1~5~1{]};}

Then, use the formula for the projection matrix to define \emph{P}:

\texttt{~~~P~=~A*inv(A'*A)*A';}

Finally, compute the projection of the given vector:

\texttt{~~~result~=~P*{[}1;~0;~0;~0{]}}
